#- Nature’s first green is gold, §0
§0Her hardest hue to hold. §0
§0Her early leaf’s a flower; §0
§0But only so an hour. §0
§0Then leaf subsides to leaf. §0
§0So Eden sank to grief, §0
§0So dawn goes down to day. §0
§0Nothing gold can stay. 
#- 